properties.headline: Lake Wind Advisory issued January 9 at 3:29AM EST until January 9 at 7:00PM EST by NWS Melbourne FL
properties.description:
* WHAT...East winds 15 to 20 mph with gusts up to 30 mph expected
over interior sections. Stronger winds are expected along the
Brevard, Indian River, Saint Lucie and Martin coasts with
sustained 20 to 25 mph and gusts of 30 to 35 mph.

* WHERE...Inland Volusia, Orange, Seminole, Southern Brevard,
Osceola, Indian River, Okeechobee, St. Lucie, Martin, Coastal
Volusia and Northern Brevard Counties.

* WHEN...From 7 AM this morning to 7 PM EST this evening.

* IMPACTS...Strong winds on area lakes and the Intracoastal waters
will create hazardous conditions for small craft. Strong winds
may blow around unsecured objects.
properties.instruction:
Boaters on area lakes should use extra caution since strong winds
and rough waves can overturn small craft. Secure trash cans, lawn
furniture, and other loose outdoor objects that can be easily
blown around by strong winds.

NWSheadline: LAKE WIND ADVISORY IN EFFECT FROM 7 AM THIS MORNING TO 7 PM EST THIS EVENING
